<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>MVA with Hypoglycaemia - AO Training Module</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-dark: #003300;
            --primary-mid: #004d00;
            --primary-light: #006600;
            --accent-green: #00994d;
            --card-bg: #f0f7f0;
            --text-dark: #1a1a1a;
            --text-light: #ffffff;
            --warning: #cc7a00;
            --critical: #cc0000;
            --highlight: #ffeb3b;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        html {
            font-size: 18px;
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f5e9 0%, #c8e6c9 100%);
            color: var(--text-dark);
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding-bottom: 60px;
        }

        /* Sticky Header */
        .sticky-header {
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            color: var(--text-light);
            padding: 12px 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 51, 0, 0.3);
        }

        .header-content {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 16px;
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .header-logo {
            width: 60px;
            height: 60px;
            object-fit: contain;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        .header-title {
            flex: 1;
        }

        .header-title h1 {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 2px;
        }

        .header-title p {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .progress-bar {
            height: 4px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
            margin-top: 12px;
        }

        .progress-fill {
            height: 100%;
            background: var(--accent-green);
            width: 0%;
            transition: width 0.3s ease;
        }

        /* Main Content */
        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* Protocol Reference Box */
        .protocol-ref {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a237e 0%, #283593 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin: 16px 0;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .protocol-ref a {
            color: var(--highlight);
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .protocol-ref a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        /* Section Styling */
        .section {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 51, 0, 0.1);
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(20px);
            transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease;
        }

        .section.visible {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: translateY(0);
        }

        .section-header {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            padding-bottom: 12px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-green);
        }

        .section-icon {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: var(--primary-dark);
        }

        h3 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--primary-mid);
            margin: 16px 0 12px 0;
        }

        /* Scenario Card */
        .scenario-card {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-dark) 0%, var(--primary-mid) 100%);
            color: var(--text-light);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .scenario-card h3 {
            color: var(--highlight);
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        /* MDT Display */
        .mdt-screen {
            background: #1a1a2e;
            color: #00ff00;
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            padding: 16px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            margin: 16px 0;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .mdt-screen .priority {
            color: #ff6b6b;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .mdt-screen .info-line {
            margin: 4px 0;
        }

        /* Checklists */
        .checklist {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .checklist li {
            padding: 12px 16px;
            margin: 8px 0;
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 12px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            min-height: 44px;
        }

        .checklist li::before {
            content: "☐";
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            font-weight: bold;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        /* Break Point Cards */
        .break-point {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff3e0 0%, #ffe0b2 100%);
            border-left: 5px solid var(--warning);
            border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 24px 0;
        }

        .break-point-header {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .break-point-badge {
            background: var(--warning);
            color: white;
            padding: 6px 14px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .break-point-type {
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 10px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
        }

        .break-point h4 {
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        /* Critical Alert */
        .critical-alert {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffebee 0%, #ffcdd2 100%);
            border-left: 5px solid var(--critical);
            border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .critical-alert h4 {
            color: var(--critical);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        /* Toggle Sections */
        .toggle-section {
            margin: 12px 0;
        }

        .toggle-btn {
            width: 100%;
            background: var(--primary-mid);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 44px;
            transition: background 0.3s ease;
        }

        .toggle-btn:hover, .toggle-btn:active {
            background: var(--primary-dark);
        }

        .toggle-btn::after {
            content: "▼";
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .toggle-btn.active::after {
            transform: rotate(180deg);
        }

        .toggle-content {
            display: none;
            padding: 20px;
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border-radius: 0 0 12px 12px;
            margin-top: -8px;
        }

        .toggle-content.show {
            display: block;
        }

        /* Skill Box */
        .skill-box {
            background: white;
            border: 2px solid var(--accent-green);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .skill-box h4 {
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .skill-box h4::before {
            content: "🔧";
        }

        /* Protocol Box */
        .protocol-box {
            background: #e8f5e9;
            border: 2px solid var(--primary-dark);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .protocol-box h4 {
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .protocol-box h4::before {
            content: "📋";
        }

        /* Steps */
        .steps {
            counter-reset: step;
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .steps li {
            position: relative;
            padding: 16px 16px 16px 50px;
            margin: 12px 0;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-green);
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .steps li::before {
            counter-increment: step;
            content: counter(step);
            position: absolute;
            left: 12px;
            top: 50%;
            transform: translateY(-50%);
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            color: white;
            width: 28px;
            height: 28px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
        }

        /* Info Box */
        .info-box {
            background: #e3f2fd;
            border-left: 4px solid #2196f3;
            padding: 16px;
            border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        /* Teaching Points */
        .teaching-points {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            padding: 16px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 12px;
        }

        .teaching-points h5 {
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .teaching-points ul {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .teaching-points li {
            margin: 6px 0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        /* Facilitator Prompt */
        .facilitator-prompt {
            background: #f3e5f5;
            border-left: 4px solid #9c27b0;
            padding: 12px 16px;
            border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
            margin: 12px 0;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .facilitator-prompt::before {
            content: "💬 Ask: ";
            font-weight: bold;
            font-style: normal;
        }

        /* Observations Table */
        .obs-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 16px 0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .obs-table th, .obs-table td {
            padding: 12px;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }

        .obs-table th {
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            color: white;
        }

        .obs-table tr:nth-child(even) {
            background: var(--card-bg);
        }

        .obs-table .abnormal {
            color: var(--critical);
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Medication Box */
        .medication-box {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff8e1 0%, #ffecb3 100%);
            border: 2px solid var(--warning);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .medication-box h4 {
            color: var(--warning);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        .dose-highlight {
            background: white;
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 8px 0;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--warning);
        }

        /* Debrief Section */
        .debrief-question {
            background: white;
            padding: 16px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 12px 0;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-green);
        }

        .debrief-question strong {
            color: var(--primary-dark);
        }

        /* Take Home Messages */
        .take-home {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-dark) 0%, var(--primary-light) 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .take-home h4 {
            color: var(--highlight);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        .take-home ul {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .take-home li {
            margin: 8px 0;
        }

        /* Equipment Grid */
        .equipment-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 12px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .equipment-item {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .equipment-item::before {
            content: "✓";
            color: var(--accent-green);
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Responsive */
        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            html {
                font-size: 16px;
            }

            .header-title h1 {
                font-size: 1rem;
            }

            .section {
                padding: 16px;
            }

            .mdt-screen {
                font-size: 0.8rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Sticky Header -->
    <header class="sticky-header">
        <div class="header-content">
            <img src="https://cdn.simtheory.ai/image/upload/v1772335546/u0301032439_IMG_5042_gz6puq.jpg" 
                 alt="DSY Training Logo" 
                 class="header-logo"
                 width="60" 
                 height="60">
            <div class="header-title">
                <h1>MVA with Hypoglycaemia</h1>
                <p>Volunteer AO Walk-Through Scenario | CPP-009-AO</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="progress-bar">
            <div class="progress-fill" id="progressFill"></div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">

        <!-- Section 1: Title & Context -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">🚑</div>
                <h2>Scenario Overview</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-ref">
                <strong>Source Protocol:</strong> Hypoglycaemia - AO (CPP-009-AO)<br>
                <a href="https://clinical.saambulance.sa.gov.au/assets/pdf/home/Hypoglycaemia%20-%20AO.pdf" target="_blank">View Protocol Document →</a>
            </div>
            
            <div class="scenario-card">
                <h3>Single Vehicle MVA — Medical Origin</h3>
                <p><strong>Setting:</strong> Rural road, late afternoon. Car has left the road and struck a tree. Caller reports the driver is confused and not responding normally.</p>
                <p><strong>Clinical Focus:</strong> Hypoglycaemia causing altered consciousness leading to MVA. C-spine precautions required due to mechanism. Airway management during transport.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Learning Objectives</h3>
            <ul class="checklist">
                <li>Recognise hypoglycaemia in a patient with altered conscious state (including trauma)</li>
                <li>Apply CPP-009-AO correctly: oral glucose if GCS adequate, IM Glucagon if not</li>
                <li>Identify when to consult EOC Clinician for Glucagon administration</li>
                <li>Perform C-spine immobilisation using collar and modified towel rolls</li>
                <li>Manage airway compromise (vomiting) during transport</li>
                <li>Deliver structured ISBAR handover at hospital</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Protocol Summary -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">📋</div>
                <h2>Protocol Summary: Hypoglycaemia - AO (CPP-009-AO)</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="toggle-section">
                <button class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleContent(this)">
                    Key Protocol Principles
                </button>
                <div class="toggle-content">
                    <h4>From CPP-009-AO:</h4>
                    <blockquote style="border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-dark); padding-left: 16px; margin: 12px 0; font-style: italic;">
                        "Hypoglycaemia can manifest as a variety of symptoms ranging from confusion, altered behaviour, and diaphoresis to unconsciousness and seizure. The appropriate management for hypoglycaemia is <strong>the least invasive therapy that increases blood glucose</strong>."
                    </blockquote>

                    <div class="info-box">
                        <strong>Critical Point:</strong> "Measure the BGL on all patients (particularly children) who have an altered conscious state or altered cerebral function, <strong>including trauma and seizures</strong>."
                    </div>

                    <h4>Normal BGL Ranges</h4>
                    <ul class="checklist">
                        <li><strong>Adults and children:</strong> Usually &gt; 3.5 mmol/L</li>
                        <li><strong>Neonates:</strong> &gt; 2.5 mmol/L</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="toggle-section">
                <button class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleContent(this)">
                    AO Treatment Pathway (Patients ≥ 2 years)
                </button>
                <div class="toggle-content">
                    <div class="protocol-box">
                        <h4>All patients ≥ 2 years with BGL &lt; 3.5 mmol/L</h4>
                        
                        <h4>Step 1: Assess swallowing ability</h4>
                        <p><strong>Key indicator:</strong> "A cough is a good indicator" of adequate GCS to swallow</p>

                        <h4>Step 2: If patient CAN swallow safely</h4>
                        <div class="dose-highlight">
                            <strong>Oral glucose up to 15 g</strong><br>
                            (glucose gel, glucose tablets, or sugary drink)
                        </div>

                        <h4>Step 3: If oral glucose CANNOT be given or is INEFFECTIVE</h4>
                        <p><strong>Consult EOC Clinician</strong> who may advise:</p>
                        
                        <div class="medication-box">
                            <h4>IM Glucagon Doses (EOC Clinician authorisation required)</h4>
                            <div class="dose-highlight">
                                <strong>≥ 6 years (or ≥ 25 kg):</strong> IM Glucagon 1 mg
                            </div>
                            <div class="dose-highlight">
                                <strong>≥ 2 years to &lt; 6 years (or &lt; 25 kg):</strong> IM Glucagon 0.5 mg
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h4>Step 4: Post-treatment</h4>
                        <ul class="checklist">
                            <li>If recovery occurs, consider offering <strong>complex carbohydrates</strong> to eat</li>
                            <li>Provide transport and notify receiving facility</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3: Equipment -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">🎒</div>
                <h2>Required Equipment</h2>
            </div>
            
            <div class="equipment-grid">
                <div class="equipment-item">Ambulance Response Bag</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Corpuls3 Monitor</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Glucometer + test strips</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Oral glucose gel (15g)</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Glucagon 1mg (IM)</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Complex carbohydrates (biscuits/sandwich)</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Semi-rigid cervical collar</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Towels × 2</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">500mL NaCl 0.9% bags × 2</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Transpore tape</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Vacuum mattress</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Stretcher</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Suction unit (portable + vehicle)</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">Yankauer suction catheter</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">PPE (gloves, eyewear)</div>
                <div class="equipment-item">ePCR tablet</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4: Pre-Brief -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">📝</div>
                <h2>Pre-Brief (≈10 minutes)</h2>
            </div>
            
            <p>Facilitator sets the scene and reviews key protocol points before commencing the walk-through.</p>
            
            <h3>Crew Briefing Points</h3>
            <ul class="checklist">
                <li>Today's scenario involves an MVA with an underlying medical cause</li>
                <li>We'll practice primary/secondary survey at the scene</li>
                <li>C-spine precautions are indicated due to mechanism of injury</li>
                <li>BGL measurement and CPP-009-AO (Hypoglycaemia) management will be key</li>
                <li>Remember: "Least invasive therapy that increases blood glucose"</li>
                <li>We'll manage an airway complication during transport</li>
                <li>Session concludes with ISBAR handover practice</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>Role Allocation:</strong><br>
                <strong>Clinician (AO1):</strong> Patient contact, history, clinical decisions, medication administration<br>
                <strong>Driver (AO2):</strong> Scene safety, observations/Corpuls3, equipment, documentation
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 5: Dispatch & En Route -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">📱</div>
                <h2>Dispatch & En Route Phase</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="mdt-screen">
                <div class="info-line"><span class="priority">● PRIORITY 2</span></div>
                <div class="info-line">TYPE: MVA — Single Vehicle vs Tree</div>
                <div class="info-line">LOCATION: Flinders Highway, 8km west of Port Lincoln</div>
                <div class="info-line">CALLER: Passing motorist</div>
                <div class="info-line">INFO: Car off road into tree. Driver confused,</div>
                <div class="info-line">      not making sense. Still in vehicle.</div>
                <div class="info-line">      No other occupants. Vehicle upright.</div>
                <div class="info-line">ACCESS: Via highway. Police/CFS en route.</div>
                <div class="info-line">HAZARDS: Traffic. Vehicle damage unknown.</div>
            </div>

            <!-- BREAK POINT 1 -->
            <div class="break-point">
                <div class="break-point-header">
                    <span class="break-point-badge">BREAK POINT 1</span>
                    <span class="break-point-type">Discussion / Planning</span>
                </div>
                <h4>En-Route Planning</h4>
                
                <div class="facilitator-prompt">
                    "You're en route, about 8 minutes out. What are you thinking? What causes a single vehicle MVA with a confused driver?"
                </div>

                <h4>Expected AO Reasoning</h4>
                <ul class="checklist">
                    <li>"Confused driver" — could be head injury, <strong>hypoglycaemia</strong>, stroke, drugs/alcohol, or post-ictal</li>
                    <li>Single vehicle MVA into tree — mechanism suggests potential C-spine injury</li>
                    <li>Need to consider both trauma AND medical causes</li>
                    <li>Protocol reminder: "Measure BGL on all patients with altered conscious state, <strong>including trauma</strong>"</li>
                    <li>Scene safety: traffic management, vehicle stability, fuel leak</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="teaching-points">
                    <h5>Key Teaching Points</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Single vehicle MVAs often have an underlying medical cause</li>
                        <li>CPP-009-AO specifically states to check BGL in trauma patients with altered consciousness</li>
                        <li>Don't let the "trauma call" blind you to medical causes</li>
                        <li>Plan for C-spine precautions until mechanism is assessed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <strong>Real-Job Translation:</strong> Use travel time productively. Brief your partner on roles. Ensure glucometer is accessible — it should be one of the first things you reach for with any altered conscious state.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 6: On Arrival -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">🚗</div>
                <h2>On Arrival — Scene Management</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="scenario-card">
                <h3>Scene Description</h3>
                <p>You arrive to find a sedan that has left the road on a gentle curve and struck a tree at moderate speed. The front end is crumpled, airbags deployed. Vehicle is upright and stable. The driver, a male approximately 55 years old, is still in the driver's seat with seatbelt on. He appears awake but is moving slowly and making incomprehensible sounds.</p>
                <p>A passing motorist is standing nearby. No other services on scene yet.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- BREAK POINT 2 -->
            <div class="break-point">
                <div class="break-point-header">
                    <span class="break-point-badge">BREAK POINT 2</span>
                    <span class="break-point-type">Discussion / Decision-Making</span>
                </div>
                <h4>Doorway / First Impressions</h4>

                <div class="facilitator-prompt">
