            <h4>Immediate Actions</h4>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li><strong>Call to driver:</strong> "Stop when safe — I need help back here!"</li>
                <li><strong>Tilt stretcher/mattress:</strong> If possible, tilt entire stretcher to side (patient + mattress together)</li>
                <li><strong>If cannot tilt:</strong> Perform log roll with mattress — keep patient IN the vacuum mattress</li>
                <li><strong>Suction immediately:</strong> Use Yankauer to clear mouth and oropharynx</li>
                <li><strong>Open airway:</strong> Jaw thrust (maintains C-spine) — do NOT head tilt</li>
                <li><strong>Reassess airway:</strong> Look, listen, feel for clear airway</li>
                <li><strong>Continue suction</strong> until airway clear</li>
                <li><strong>Reassess breathing:</strong> SpO2, chest rise, air entry</li>
            </ol>

            <div class="skill-box">
                <h4>Log Roll for Airway Clearance</h4>
                <p><strong>Modified technique when patient in vacuum mattress:</strong></p>
                <ol class="steps">
                    <li>Person 1 (at head): Controls head/neck movement — coordinates all movement</li>
                    <li>Person 2 (if available): Supports shoulders and hip</li>
                    <li>On command from Person 1: Roll patient AND mattress together as a unit (approximately 45°)</li>
                    <li>Allow vomit to drain from mouth — gravity assists</li>
                    <li>Suction as material drains</li>
                    <li>Return to supine only when airway is clear</li>
                </ol>
                <p><strong>Key point:</strong> The vacuum mattress maintains spinal alignment during the roll — use it to your advantage</p>
            </div>

            <div class="toggle-section">
