                </button>
                <div class="toggle-content">
                    <h4>Effective Suctioning</h4>
                    <ul class="checklist">
                        <li>Use rigid Yankauer catheter for oropharyngeal suction</li>
                        <li>Insert catheter only as far as you can see</li>
                        <li>Apply suction while withdrawing — not while inserting</li>
                        <li>Limit suction to 10-15 seconds at a time</li>
                        <li>Reassess airway between suction attempts</li>
                        <li>Clear catheter with water if blocked</li>
                        <li>Monitor SpO2 — prolonged suctioning causes desaturation</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Jaw Thrust (C-spine safe)</h4>
                    <ul class="checklist">
                        <li>Position yourself at head of patient</li>
                        <li>Place fingers behind angle of mandible (jaw)</li>
                        <li>Lift jaw forward and upward</li>
                        <li>Use thumbs to open mouth if needed</li>
                        <li>This opens airway WITHOUT moving the neck</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

